The All Progressives Congress (APC), on Tuesday, held its presidential campaign rally in Owerri, the Imo capital. While in Imo, President Muhammadu Buhari was conferred with the chieftaincy title of ‘Nwanne Di Na Mba’ (a brother in diaspora) by Emmanuel Okeke, the Eze Imo. Bola Tinubu, the presidential candidate of the party; Hope Uzodimma, Imo governor; Babajide Sanwo-Olu, Lagos governor; David Umahi, Ebonyi governor, and Adamu Abdullahi, APC national chairperson, were also in Imo. Below are pictures from the events.           